<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}-{2}{y}=-{10}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{6}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},-{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+-{2}{y}=-{10}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}=-{10}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{10}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{\left(\frac{{-{10}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{9}}\right)}+{6}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{8}}{{9}}\cdot{\left(-{10}\right)}--\frac{{8}}{{9}}{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+{6}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8.8888888888889}-{\left(-{1.7777777777778}\right)}{y}+{6}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.7777777777778}{y}+{\left({6}\right)}{y}=-{8}-{8.8888888888889}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.7777777777778}{y}+{\left({6}\right)}{y}=-{16.888888888889}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1.7777777777778}+{\left({6}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{16.888888888889}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4.2222222222222}{y}=-{16.888888888889}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{16.888888888889}}{{4.2222222222222}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+-{2}{\left(-{4}\right)}=-{10}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{\left({8}\right)}=-{10}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}=-{10}-{\left({8}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{18}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},-{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

